In the [Eucalyptus Architecture Overview|http://packages.release.eucalyptus-systems.com/documentation/origin/master/#install-guide/euca_architecture.html] section:
{quote}
Riak CS clusters provide an alternative to Walrus as an object storage provider. SAN clusters are available to Eucalyptus subscribers.
{quote}
In feedback, Garrett said:
{quote}
This implies SANs can provide object storage. They cannot.
{quote}
... there's a subtle point here that I am not understanding. [~gholms] [~swathi] - please help me clarify. (Also, no mention of Ceph-RGW here, as another alternative.)

To use the [admin roles|http://docs.hpcloud.com/eucalyptus/4.2.1/admin-guide/personas.html] feature, one creates a new account and grants it permission to assume those roles rather than creating a new user in the eucalyptus account.  More specifically, replace the instructions with the following

# If it does not already exist, create the euca2ools configuration directory.  {code}mkdir ~/.euca{code}
# Create a new account for administration purposes.  {code}euare-accountcreate -wld DOMAIN ACCOUNT > ~/.euca/FILE.ini{code}
#* DOMAIN must match  the DNS domain chosen in the "Configure DNS" section.
#* ACCOUNT is the name of the new account.
#* FILE can be anything.  We recommend a descriptive name that includes the new account's name and the "admin" user which the account will come with.
# Grant the new account's "admin" user permission to assume Eucalyptus's administration roles.  {code}clcadmin-grant-admin-access -a ACCOUNT -u admin{code}
#* ACCOUNT is the name of the account created in the previous step.
# Switch to the new account's admin user:{code}
eval `euare-releaserole`
export AWS_DEFAULT_REGION=admin@REGION
{code}
#* REGION must match the region name from the previous step.  By default, this is the same as the cloud's DNS domain chosen in "Configure DNS".
# Assume the {{InfrastructureAdministrator}} role to continue the setup process.  {code}eval `euare-assumerole eucalyptus:role/InfrastructureAdministrator`{code}

----

These instructions make a few assumptions:
# The new cloud's administrator wants to use the "admin" user in an account for day-to-day administration.
# The "admin" user above should be able to assume all administration roles.  Unless instructed otherwise, {{clcadmin-grant-admin-access}} grants access to all of them.
# The {{InfrastructureAdministrator}} role is sufficient to complete the cloud setup process.  Someone more familiar with the administration roles' capabilities, such as [~sjones], may be able to answer that question for sure.

[~sjones] - on this page: http://docs.hpcloud.com/eucalyptus/4.3.0/#install-guide/preparing_firewalls.html [~gholms] asks about this entry - can you help?
{quote}
TCP 8773	Web services port for the CLC, user-facing services (UFS), object storage gateway (OSG), Walrus SC; also used for external and internal communications by the CLC and Walrus. Configurable with euctl.
{quote}
"euctl may only be able to add a second port - check with [~sjones]"
